This paper discusses algorithmic machine teaching, which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper focuses on developing a framework for understanding the different teaching models and complexity measures used in batch and sequential settings. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper involves complexity analysis, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
